devdoc.title: BikeShare Contract

acceptProposal(address,uint256,string,st.notice: Accepts a proposal and initiates the bike rental process.

activate(string,string).notice: Activates the contract and sets the GPS location of the contract owner

cancelLending().notice: Cancels the lending process initiated by the lender.

cancelProposal(address).notice: Cancels a proposal with a specific bike rent contract address.

cancelledRenting(address).notice: Cancels the renting process initiated by the renter.

claimRewards().notice: Claim the accumulated rewards for the contract owner.

confirmBikeReturned(string).notice: Confirms definitaly the bike has been returned and the deposit is returned to the renter.

confirmBikeTaken(string).notice: Confirms the bike has been taken by the renter.

deleteOldProposals().notice: Deletes old proposals that are no longer valid.

depositW2R(uint256).notice: Deposits W2R tokens to the contract

destroy().notice: Destroy the contract, W2R funds are transfered to the owner. In case of a rental, destruction is only possible after the rental time + 2 days, in case of a delay. After this delay, and if the bike has not been returned, lender can destroy the contract but deposit will be send to the vault, waiting to know who failed (renter stole the bike, or lender went away to keep the deposit) So, this functionnality prevents the use of the destruction function to steal the deposit.

getProposalsLength().notice: Returns the length of the proposals array.

getRentalsByAdresses(address).notice: Returns the number of rentals for a given renter address.

getRentalsLength(address).notice: Returns the length of the rentals array for a specific renter.

getTotalRewards().notice: Returns the total rewards accumulated by the contract

returnedBike(address).notice: Declares the bike has been returned by the renter. People have to be physically present at the meeting point

setDepositAmount(uint256).notice: Allows the owner to set the deposit amount.

setGPS(string,string).notice: Sets the GPS location of the contract owner

setMaximumRental(uint256).notice: Allows the owner to set the maximum rental duration in days

setProposal(address,uint256,uint256,uint.notice: Allows a renter to submit a rental proposal.

setRate(uint256).notice: Allows the owner to set the rental rate.

withdrawFunds(uint256).notice: Allows the owner to withdraw funds from the contract.

userdoc.notice: This contract manages bike rentals and related operations.
